---
import DocLayout from "../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout title="Configuration">
  <h1>Repository configuration</h1>
  <p>
    For project-wide defaults, create <code>.github/resource-translator.yml</code>.
    Action inputs always win when both are provided. Override the path with the
    <code>configPath</code> input if needed.
  </p>

  <h2>Schema</h2>
<pre><code>{`# .github/resource-translator.yml
sourceLocale: en
toLocales:
  - fr
  - de
  - es
include:
  - "src/**/*.en.json"
  - "apps/**/*.en.resx"
exclude:
  - "**/__tests__/**"
glossary:
  Acme: Contoso
  Octocat: Octocat   # keep brand names verbatim
categoryId: my-custom-translator-category
apiVersion: "3.0"`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Field reference</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>sourceLocale</code></td><td>string</td><td>Falls back to the <code>sourceLocale</code> input if not set.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>toLocales</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>Either an array or a comma-separated string.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>include</code> / <code>exclude</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>Glob patterns evaluated against absolute and workspace-relative paths.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>glossary</code></td><td>map&lt;string,string&gt;</td><td>Post-translation term overrides. Word-boundary aware (handles <code>C++</code>, <code>.NET</code>).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>categoryId</code></td><td>string</td><td>Azure Custom Translator category. Sent as <code>?category=...</code>.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>apiVersion</code></td><td>string</td><td>Translator REST API version. Defaults to <code>3.0</code>.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Loading order</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>The action reads explicit inputs from the workflow.</li>
    <li>It loads the YAML config from <code>configPath</code>.</li>
    <li>For every shared field, the input wins; otherwise the YAML value is used.</li>
  </ol>
</DocLayout>
